      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im struggling with a python script. i'm trying to process these massive csv files using pandas but i keep hitting a MemoryError when i try to load the whole thing at once. i think i need to switch to something more efficient, maybe generators? what's the actual difference between using a list comprehension vs a generator expression when it comes to the memory footprint? thanks",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The core difference is how they store data in memory. A list comprehension builds an entire list in memory at once, meaning it consumes memory proportional to the size of the resulting dataset. In contrast, a generator expression creates an iterator that yields one item at a time only when requested, keeping the memory footprint extremely low regardless of the file's size. For massive CSVs, generators are the superior choice because they process data lazily, preventing that dreaded `MemoryError`.",
      "source": "target",
